[{"question":"Who thinks sex is bad?","answer":"Not me.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":8,"aSentId":9},{"question":"Penn Jillette, how are you?","answer":"Oh, why I -- I\u0027m just so excited to have Rush and sex below my picture --","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":63,"aSentId":64},{"question":"What is the concept then?","answer":"The concept is that sex is bad.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":95,"aSentId":96},{"question":"Well, who thinks sex is bad?","answer":"Not me.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":97,"aSentId":98},{"question":"Is it?","answer":"Yes, I agree --","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":110,"aSentId":111},{"question":"-- when you -- when you take religion to its extremities?","answer":"Well, I -- I actually think that this does certainly -- anti-sex does start often in religion.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":116,"aSentId":117},{"question":"You would?","answer":"How many times he has sex.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":120,"aSentId":121},{"question":"You would?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":122,"aSentId":123},{"question":"Once you\u0027ve said sex is a bad thing -- doesn\u0027t all of this follow logically?","answer":"But there can\u0027t be anybody in the world who genuinely thinks sex is a bad thing.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":151,"aSentId":152},{"question":"That it\u0027s a bad thing?","answer":"Sure.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":154,"aSentId":155},{"question":"Or a bad thing outside of wedlock?","answer":"Well, sure.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":158,"aSentId":159},{"question":"It\u0027s one of the great wonders of the world, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"Absolutely.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":163,"aSentId":164},{"question":"As an atheist, when you see that happening politically, and these are people who may one day be your president -- what do you think?","answer":"Well, you have to -- it\u0027s very, very hard not to just be told you so.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":175,"aSentId":176},{"question":"Are there elements of a religious conviction which you think could be helpful to somebody as a political leader?","answer":"You have to have the passion for freedom greater than the passion for you know what\u0027s right.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":228,"aSentId":229},{"question":"Can I join you here?","answer":"Yes, you may.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":241,"aSentId":242},{"question":"But the better way for America to go now is to collectively put all this brain power together and think, how do we keep this country where it should be, a great country?","answer":"I think that I always go with individualism.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":263,"aSentId":264},{"question":"What has gone wrong with the American Dream?","answer":"You know, I don\u0027t know.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":270,"aSentId":271},{"question":"So, Kal, what\u0027s more fun -- working with Hugh Laurie on \"House,\" being in a hit movie, or running in the corridors of power with the president?","answer":"Probably different kinds of fun, I would say.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":345,"aSentId":346},{"question":"If I held a metaphorical bullet to your head and you could only do one of these things the rest of your life -- movies, TV, politics?","answer":"I would get rid of TV and I would choose between movies and politics.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":351,"aSentId":352},{"question":"Which one is it going to be?","answer":"One is fact and one is fiction.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":353,"aSentId":354},{"question":"Would you?","answer":"Because you\u0027re helping real people with real substantive things.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":357,"aSentId":358},{"question":"What\u0027s it been like in there to be at the center of things looking out with everybody else wondering what\u0027s going on in there?","answer":"It\u0027s been pretty remarkable.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":361,"aSentId":362},{"question":"What would you say are the common misconceptions about the president?","answer":"Oh, gosh.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":368,"aSentId":369},{"question":"Do you accept that as a criticism?","answer":"No, I don\u0027t think so.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":385,"aSentId":386},{"question":"ORGAN: What kind of guy is he when the door shuts?","answer":"The same.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":395,"aSentId":396},{"question":"Who would you most like to come up against?","answer":"To me, all of the candidates are the same, just in terms of the policy.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":452,"aSentId":453},{"question":"You\u0027re a busy guy, aren\u0027t you?","answer":"I try to keep busy.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":526,"aSentId":527},{"question":"What is rotten, do you think?","answer":"Well, I have a -- I\u0027m a father of six children.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":546,"aSentId":547},{"question":"If I asked you, for example, what your view of gay marriage is, what would you say?","answer":"Go ahead and ask me.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":572,"aSentId":573},{"question":"What is your view of gay marriage?","answer":"I feel like I just got imported into the Christine O\u0027Donnell interview you did back in August.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":574,"aSentId":575},{"question":"Would you tell them that gay marriage is a sin?","answer":"I would tell my children, as -- I tell them what I believe myself.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":580,"aSentId":581},{"question":"What do you believe?","answer":"I believe that marriage was defined by God a long time ago.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":583,"aSentId":584},{"question":"Do you think homosexuality is a sin?","answer":"I think that it\u0027s -- it\u0027s unnatural.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":591,"aSentId":592},{"question":"So what\u0027s your view of abortion?","answer":"I think that it\u0027s wrong.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":617,"aSentId":618},{"question":"Under any circumstances?","answer":"Under any circumstances.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":619,"aSentId":620},{"question":"Even rape and incest?","answer":"I think someone who is ultimately willing to murder a child, even to fix another tragic end, a devastating situation like rape or incest or things like that, is not taking the moral high road.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":621,"aSentId":622},{"question":"Could you honestly look a daughter in the eye if she was raped and say you have got to have that child?","answer":"AMERON: Yes, and I will help you.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":624,"aSentId":625},{"question":"You would do that?","answer":"Yes, of course.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":626,"aSentId":627},{"question":"Whose do you take?","answer":"I take my values.","docId":"120302pmt","qSentId":668,"aSentId":669}]